reviews.review_text: Where has this source been all this time? Hey GD folks,     wow,  a great solid east coast performance. It's a real treat to get a nice PCM source that is clean, so many of these tapes suffer from drop outs and bad transfers.  This one sounds like it was recorded yesterday; nice upfront sound and captures those Phil bombs very accurately; it's tough to get those far from the stage.  The only drawback is the mic's are not that high above the crowd so there are some hand claps, etc.  but it's a barnburner rock and roll show what da ya expect.  The GD deliver and Siberman grants us the only digital audience source, a big thanks for hauling that stuff in and a big thanks for Miller and Co. for the leg work transfers.
